---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Terms of Service" description="The terms for using Storyteller Toolbox — short, honest, and in plain language.">
  <article class="policy">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="effective">Effective 2026-07-11 · applies to storytellertoolbox.com</p>

    <h2>The service</h2>
    <p>
      Storyteller Toolbox is a free set of tools for tabletop game masters, solo players,
      writers, and worldbuilders: generators, oracles, and a document workspace (the Sheet
      Builder — growing toward maps, stat blocks, initiative trackers, and broader
      worldbuilding documents). By using the site you accept these terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Your content is yours</h2>
    <p>
      Everything you create here — sheets, notes, journals, prayers, campaigns, worlds —
      belongs to you, entirely. We claim no rights to it and take no license over it. The
      site's one job with your data is <strong>storing your progress so you can continue
      across devices</strong>: locally in your browser, and optionally in a single file in
      your own Google Drive. We never receive, evaluate, sell, share, or otherwise use
      your content — see the <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> for the full
      commitment and the architecture that enforces it.
    </p>

    <h2>Your responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Keep your own backups of what matters.</strong> Local data lives in your
        browser and can be lost to cleared site data; the Drive backup is under your
        control (Google Drive retains prior revisions of the backup file for a limited
        time, which helps with accidents).
      </li>
      <li>
        Use the site and its Google Drive integration as intended — don't attempt to
        disrupt the service, misuse the integration, or circumvent its single-file scope.
      </li>
      <li>You're responsible for the content you create and how you use it.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Generated content</h2>
    <p>
      The generators compose results from community-contributed and original tables
      (attributions on the <a href="/about/">About page</a>). Generated output is fiction
      offered as inspiration — use it freely in your games and writing. If you contributed
      to a source list and want something removed,
      <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/seriousd6/">get in touch</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>No warranty</h2>
    <p>
      The site is a hobby project provided <strong>as is</strong>, free of charge, with no
      warranties of any kind — including availability, fitness for a particular purpose,
      or that your data will never be lost. To the maximum extent permitted by law, the
      operator is not liable for any damages arising from use of the site. Features may
      change, break, or be retired.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes &amp; contact</h2>
    <p>
      These terms may be updated as the tool grows; the current version always lives at
      this page with its effective date. Continued use after a change means acceptance.
      Questions: <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/seriousd6/">u/seriousd6</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .policy {
    max-width: 46rem;
  }

  .policy h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    color: var(--color-statblock);
  }

  .effective {
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }

  .policy ul {
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-block: var(--space-4);
  }
</style>
